/*
 * BYOBYOK - a minimal text editor / electric typewriter for the M5PaperS3
 * ("Bring Your Own [keyboard to your] Bring Your Own Keyboard")
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * - Boots to a menu: "[ New file ]" + every *.txt on the microSD card.
 * - Plain-text editing with a real USB keyboard (USB-C OTG host).
 * - ESC opens an in-editor menu: Resume / Save / Save & exit / Discard & exit.
 * - Word/character count popup on Ctrl+W; battery + clock in the status bar.
 * - Auto-save every 20s for named files (clears the unsaved "*" marker).
 * - Rename (r) and delete (Del) files from the main menu.
 * - Files are stored on the microSD card root, FAT32.
 * - Novel-sized files: the document lives in a PSRAM gap buffer and edits
 *   re-wrap only the touched paragraph, so multi-MB files stay responsive.
 *   (Text-core logic is unit-tested on the host - see tests/.)
 * - Bluetooth (BLE) keyboards: pair from the menu ('b' or tap the BT button).
 *   Optional - needs NimBLE-Arduino >= 2.0, or set ENABLE_BLE_KEYBOARD 0.
 * - QWERTY / Dvorak / Colemak layouts; Enter auto-saves (5 s throttle).
 * - Reader can rotate to portrait ('r' in the reader, or the menu button).
 * - UTF-8 files are folded to ASCII on load (curly quotes -> ', em-dash ->
 *   --, cafe accents stripped): the built-in fonts are 7-bit.
 * - Spell check (Ctrl+K) against /wordlist.txt on the SD card.
 * - Cloud sync ('c'): joins WiFi from /sync.cfg, HTTP-PUTs drafts (WebDAV).
 * - USB drive mode ('u'): reboots into TinyUSB MSC, SD card appears as a
 *   USB stick. Optional - set ENABLE_USB_DRIVE 0 to compile without.
 *
 * Keys
 *   Type / Enter / Backspace / Tab .... edit text
 *   Arrows / Home / End / Delete ...... move & delete
 *   Shift (or Ctrl) + arrows .......... jump a whole word
 *   Shift (or Ctrl) + Bksp / Del ...... delete a whole word
 *   Ctrl+S ........................... quick save
 *   Ctrl+W ........................... word/character count popup
 *   Ctrl+Z ........................... undo
 *   Ctrl+F ........................... find (case-insensitive, wraps)
 *   Ctrl+G ........................... writing goal / sprint
 *   Ctrl+Home / Ctrl+End ............. jump to start / end of document
 *   Ctrl+A / Ctrl+E .................. start / end of paragraph
 *   PgUp / PgDn ...................... move a screenful (page shown in bar)
 *   Ctrl+P ........................... go to a page number
 *   Ctrl+R ........................... redraw any screen (manual de-ghost)
 *   Option/Alt combos ................ accents & Esperanto (see README)
 *   Tap the editor page .............. place the cursor there
 *   ESC .............................. menu (incl. Focus mode toggle)
 *   In the main menu:  j = today's journal,  s = writing stats
 *   Shortcuts follow the active layout (Dvorak/Colemak), not key position.
 *   In the menu:  r = rename,  Del/d = delete (on a selected file)
 *
 * Libraries (Arduino IDE):
 *   - M5Unified  (>= 0.2.5)
 *   - M5GFX      (>= 0.2.7  -> built-in e-ink driver, no EPDiy needed)
 *   - EspUsbHost (by Masayuki Tanaka)
 * Board: "M5PaperS3"   |   PSRAM: OPI PSRAM (enabled)
 *
 * See README.md for setup, flashing, and USB-power troubleshooting.
 */

